#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:219
msgid "Your Check Credits"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:220
msgid "This shows your available checks and current usage. Monitor your usage to stay within limits. You will see warnings if the estimated amount of checks is higher than your credits."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:221
msgid "Recent Changes"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:222
msgid "Your latest detected changes appear here. You'll see visual comparisons highlighting what changed on your site."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:225
msgid "Auto Update Checks Status"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:226
msgid "This shows the current status of your WordPress auto-update checks. When enabled, WebChange Detector will automatically monitor your site before and after WordPress updates to detect any visual changes or issues."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:227
msgid "On-Demand Checks & Auto Update Settings"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:228
msgid "You can start the On-Demand Checks here. But first, let's walk through each important setting."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:229
msgid "Enable Auto Update Checks"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:230
msgid "Please turn this ON to enable automatic checks during WordPress auto-updates. This is required to continue the wizard. You can always turn it off later if you don't want to use it."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:231
msgid "Enabled Auto Updates"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:232
msgid "Here you see a list of all enabled auto updates. Enable or disable the auto updates in the WordPress settings."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:233
#: admin/partials/templates/update-settings.php:69
msgid "Auto Update Timeframe"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:234
msgid "Set the time window when WordPress is allowed to perform auto-updates. WebChange Detector will check your site during this period. For example: 2:00 AM - 4:00 AM when traffic is low."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:235
msgid "Weekday Selection"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:236
msgid "Choose which days WordPress can perform auto-updates. Many prefer weekdays to avoid weekend issues, or specific days when support is available."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:237
msgid "Notification Emails"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:238
msgid "Enter email addresses to receive notifications about auto-update check results. You can add multiple emails separated by commas."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:239
#: admin/partials/templates/auto-settings.php:212
#: admin/partials/templates/update-settings.php:145
msgid "Change Detection Threshold"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:240
msgid "Set the sensitivity for detecting changes (0-100%). Note: even small changes like 0.1% can be significant on long pages."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:241
#: admin/partials/templates/update-settings.php:169
msgid "CSS Injection"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:242
msgid "Add custom CSS to hide dynamic elements before screenshots (like dates, counters, ads). Example: .dynamic-date { display: none !important; }"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:243
msgid "URL Selection Table"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:244
msgid "Select which pages to monitor. Toggle Desktop/Mobile options for each URL. Pro tip: Start with your most important pages like homepage, contact, and key product pages."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:245
msgid "Save Your Settings"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:246
msgid "Don't forget to save! Your settings will be applied to both on-demand checks and auto-update monitoring."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:249
msgid "Automatic Monitoring Settings"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:250
msgid "Set up automatic monitoring to regularly check your website for unexpected changes. This is perfect for detecting hacks, broken layouts, or content issues."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:251
#: admin/partials/templates/auto-settings.php:33
msgid "Enable Monitoring"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:252
msgid "Please turn this ON to activate automatic monitoring. This is required to continue the wizard. Your selected pages will be checked regularly based on your schedule settings."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:253
msgid "Check Frequency"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:254
msgid "How often should we check your site? Daily (24h) is recommended for most sites. High-traffic sites may want more frequent checks."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:255
msgid "Preferred Check Time"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:256
msgid "Choose when checks should run. Pick a low-traffic time like 3 AM to minimize impact on visitors."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:257
msgid "Change Sensitivity"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:258
msgid "Set how sensitive the monitoring should be. Note: even 0.1% changes can be significant on long pages."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:259
msgid "Alert Recipients"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:260
msgid "Who should be notified when changes are detected? Add multiple emails separated by commas. Include your developer and key stakeholders."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:261
msgid "CSS Customization"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:262
msgid "Hide dynamic content that changes frequently (timestamps, visitor counters, etc.) to avoid false positives in monitoring."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:263
msgid "Save Monitoring Settings"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:264
msgid "Save your configuration to activate monitoring. Changes take effect immediately."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:265
msgid "Select Pages to Monitor"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:266
msgid "Choose which pages to monitor automatically. Select your most critical pages - homepage, checkout, contact forms, and high-traffic content."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:269
msgid "Change Detection History"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:270
msgid "This is your change detection hub. View all detected changes with visual comparisons showing exactly what changed, when, and by how much."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:271
msgid "Detection Table"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:272
msgid "Each row shows a detected change. Click on any row to see before/after screenshots with differences highlighted. The filters above help you find specific changes."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:273
msgid "Filter Options"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:274
msgid "Use these filters to find specific changes by date, check type, status, or to show only changes with differences."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:277
msgid "Activity Logs"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:278
msgid "Track all WebChange Detector activities - scheduled checks, on-demand checks, API calls, and system events. Essential for troubleshooting."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:279
msgid "Log Details"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:280
msgid "Each entry shows: timestamp, action type, status (success/error), and details. Green entries show successful operations, red indicates errors."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:283
msgid "URL Management"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:284
msgid "Control which content types appear in your URL list. Add custom post types, taxonomies, or WooCommerce products for monitoring."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:285
msgid "URL Synchronization"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:286
msgid "WebChange Detector syncs your site's URLs automatically. Use \"Sync Now\" after adding new content or if URLs are missing."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:287
msgid "Quick Access"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:288
msgid "The admin bar menu provides quick access to WebChange Detector from your site's frontend. Disable if you prefer a cleaner toolbar."
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:289
msgid "API Connection"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:290
msgid "Your API token connects this site to WebChange Detector's screenshot service. Keep it secret and secure!"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:291
msgid "Setup Complete!"
msgstr ""

#: admin/class-webchangedetector-admin-wordpress.php:292
